## 5. Using AI-Generated Content in Commercial Products

### 5.1 Risk Assessment

Before incorporating AI-generated content into commercial products, services, or client deliverables, the following risks must be assessed:

| Risk | Mitigation |
|------|------------|
| No copyright protection | AI-generated content may not be protectable — competitors could freely copy it |
| Third-party IP infringement | AI may reproduce copyrighted material from its training data |
| Misleading or deceptive conduct (ACL) | Passing off AI-generated content as human-created may breach the ACL |
| Client expectations | Clients may expect human-authored deliverables unless AI use is disclosed |
| Accuracy and liability | AI-generated content may contain errors — {{ business_name }} remains liable |

### 5.2 Approval Requirements

| Content Use | Approval Required | Additional Steps |
|-------------|-------------------|------------------|
| Internal use only | Team manager | Review for accuracy |
| External communications (non-commercial) | {{ ai_governance_contact if ai_governance_contact else "AI governance contact" }} | Review for accuracy + IP check |
| Commercial products or client deliverables | {{ ai_governance_contact if ai_governance_contact else "AI governance contact" }} + legal review | Full IP risk assessment + client disclosure |
| Marketing materials | Marketing lead + {{ ai_governance_contact if ai_governance_contact else "AI governance contact" }} | ACL compliance check + disclosure review |

{% if ai_in_marketing %}
{{ business_name }} uses AI in marketing. All AI-generated marketing content must be reviewed for ACL compliance, including ensuring claims are not misleading and images are not deceptive.
{% endif %}

