## 6. Third-Party IP Risks

### 6.1 AI Training Data Concerns

AI models are trained on large datasets that may include copyrighted material. When {{ business_name }} uses AI-generated outputs, there is a risk that those outputs reproduce or closely resemble third-party copyrighted works.

**Mitigation measures:**

- [ ] Do not use AI outputs verbatim for substantial portions of commercial content without human review and modification
- [ ] Run AI-generated text through plagiarism detection tools before publication
- [ ] For AI-generated images, conduct reverse image searches to check for similarity to existing works
- [ ] For AI-generated code, review for licence-restricted code snippets (GPL, LGPL, AGPL)
- [ ] Document the AI tool and prompts used to generate commercial content (for legal defensibility)
- [ ] Where possible, prefer AI tools whose vendors provide IP indemnification

### 6.2 Code-Specific IP Risks

| Risk | Mitigation |
|------|------------|
| AI-generated code may contain GPL-licensed snippets | Scan AI-generated code with licence compliance tools (e.g., FOSSA, Snyk) |
| AI-generated code may reproduce proprietary code from training data | Review AI code suggestions against known codebases before committing |
| Open-source licence obligations may be triggered | Maintain an SBOM that includes AI-generated code components |

