## 9. Trade Secrets Protection

### 9.1 Risks When Using AI Tools

| Risk | Description |
|------|-------------|
| Data leakage to AI providers | Proprietary information entered into AI prompts may be stored, logged, or used for model training |
| Loss of trade secret status | Information shared with an AI provider without confidentiality protections may lose its trade secret status |
| Competitive intelligence exposure | Patterns of AI queries may reveal {{ business_name }}'s strategic priorities or methods |

### 9.2 Protective Measures

- [ ] Never enter trade secrets, proprietary formulas, or confidential business strategies into AI tools without confirmed training opt-out
- [ ] Use on-premises or private AI deployments for processing trade secret information where available
- [ ] Ensure all AI vendor agreements include confidentiality obligations covering input data
- [ ] Classify and label trade secret information so staff can identify it before entering it into AI tools
- [ ] Conduct periodic audits of AI tool usage to detect potential trade secret disclosures

